ROTH.C — License Notice

This repository contains two kinds of material under two different terms.


PART 1 — THE RECONSTRUCTED ENGINE
(roth_c/src/engine/, roth_c/src/data/, and docs/reference/)

These files are a reconstruction, in C, of the behavior of the engine of the 1996 game
"Realms of the Haunting". They were produced by studying the game's original executable and
are, by nature, a derivative representation of that program's design and behavior. The
copyright in the underlying game and its program remains with its rights holders; nothing in
this repository grants, transfers, or diminishes any of their rights.

This material is published for the purposes of preservation, study, and interoperability —
enabling lawfully obtained copies of the game to run on modern systems. It is provided in the
spirit of long-standing community practice around the preservation of historical software.

  - No game assets are included. The game's content files (graphics, sounds, maps, text,
    music, videos) are not in this repository or its releases and must be obtained from a
    lawfully acquired copy of the game.
  - No warranty of any kind is provided.
  - Redistribution of this material should preserve this notice.
  - If you are a rights holder of "Realms of the Haunting" and have concerns about this
    repository, please open an issue or contact the repository maintainers; concerns will be
    addressed promptly and in good faith.

No license under the rights holders' copyrights is granted or implied. To play the game you
must own it.


